Add explicit declaration for getexecname in libbacktrace/fileline.c.
On macOS, getexecname() exists as a symbol but is not declared in any
public header.  When HAVE_GETEXECNAME is defined by configure, the call
site lacks a visible declaration, causing clang to infer an implicit
int return type and then fail with -Wint-conversion when assigning to
const char *.  Add an explicit extern declaration in the #else branch
so the function is properly typed on all platforms.
--- a/libbacktrace/fileline.c
+++ b/libbacktrace/fileline.c
@@ -52,6 +52,8 @@
 
 #ifndef HAVE_GETEXECNAME
 #define getexecname() NULL
+#else
+extern const char *getexecname (void);
 #endif
 
 #if !defined (HAVE_KERN_PROC_ARGS) && !defined (HAVE_KERN_PROC)
